<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 9000 Pro Sleeper After 05/01/1997, and 9800 Model After 07/01/1997 -
        REMOVE AND INSTALL - BLOWER RESISTORS - CAB (MOUNTED IN BLEND-AIR UNIT)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BLOWER RESISTORS - CAB (MOUNTED IN BLEND-AIR UNIT)</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch and blower motor switch are in the OFF position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the passenger seat and Blend-Air unit cover. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_17.xml" xrefid="hl1602007">BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER, Remove</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the blower speed resistor housing up and out of the Blend-Air unit (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602037">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connector from the resistor pack (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602047">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two screws that secure the resistor pack to the resistor housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602037" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Blower Speed Resistor Housing Remove/Install</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1602047" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602047A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Electrical Connector in Resistor Pack</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure a new resistor pack to the resistor housing with the screws removed in Step 5 of
                    Remove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the electrical connector to the resistor pack (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602047">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the resistor housing into its opening in the Blend-Air unit (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602037">Figure 41</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>In the following step, to verify correct blower operation at the air duct outlets, the cover
                        must be in place on the Blend-Air unit.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Test for correct blower operation.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install Blend-Air unit cover and passenger seat. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16020_17.xml" xrefid="hl1602006">BLEND-AIR UNIT COVER, Install</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
